
CXF-RS 3.2.4
OpenAPI 3.0 

Used employeesList.json file to create POJO to create and send it back as Response. (Bottom UP approach)
jsonschema2pojo-maven-plugin to convert from json file to pojo object.

----
http://localhost:8080/api/v1/person/456
----
http://localhost:8080/api/v1/jsonperson/100
----
http://localhost:8080/api/openapi.json
---

----------
Client:
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/postemployee/ with employee json payload (using POSTMAN)
HelloWorldServiceImpl will receive a JSON and invoke POST REST SERVICE (http://localhost:8080/api/v1/process/employee)
thru HttpURLConnection